100
00:05:55.740 --> 00:05:59.720
tumors exhibit both greater variability in telomere length among

101
00:05:59.800 --> 00:06:03.400
cancer cells and shorter telomeres in the surrounding

102
00:06:03.620 --> 00:06:07.144
stromal tissue.In parallel, her

103
00:06:07.204 --> 00:06:10.784
epidemiological studies demonstrated that long-term statin use

104
00:06:11.164 --> 00:06:14.934
is associated with a reduced risk of aggressive disease, and this is

105
00:06:14.964 --> 00:06:18.224
supported by complementary laboratory findings.

106
00:06:19.204 --> 00:06:23.184
She's also led studies identifying existing FDA-approved drugs that might be

107
00:06:23.284 --> 00:06:26.324
repurposed for cancer prevention or treatment.

108
00:06:26.914 --> 00:06:30.544
Through a multidisciplinary approach combining laboratory screening and

109
00:06:30.724 --> 00:06:34.164
epidemiological investigation, she and her colleagues identified the

110
00:06:34.764 --> 00:06:38.304
cardiac medication digoxin as a potential candidate for targeting

111
00:06:38.423 --> 00:06:41.784
prostate cancer pathways. Dr. Platz's impact

112
00:06:41.884 --> 00:06:45.864
